alized": false, "mention": "luzindole", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9996546506881714, "span": {"begin": 559, "end": 568}}, {"id": ["mesh:C495856"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993740916252136, "span": {"begin": 589, "end": 617}}, {"id": ["mesh:D008550"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "melatonin", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9995549321174622, "span": {"begin": 718, "end": 727}}, {"id": ["mesh:C495856"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9992949962615967, "span": {"begin": 739, "end": 767}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "quail", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.39837566018104553, "span": {"begin": 874, "end": 879}}, {"id": ["mesh:D008550"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "melatonin", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9905836582183838, "span": {"begin": 897, "end": 906}}, {"id": ["mesh:C495856"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9992456436157227, "span": {"begin": 952, "end": 980}}], "text": "CYP7B inhibitor (ketoconazole, 10-4 M) decreased the synthesis of 7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone in vitro&nbsp;(Tsutsui et al., 2008; Matsunaga et al., 2008; Toyoda et al., 2012).  CYP7B inhibitor (intracerebroventricular injection of ketoconazole, 5 &mu;g, from 5 AM to 6 AM) decreased the synthesis of 7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone in the brain (quail) in vivo&nbsp;(Tsutsui et al., 2008).  CYP7B activity is regulated (inhibited) by melatonin in male quail. When male quail brains were injected (intracerebroventricular) with a melatonin receptor antagonist (luzindole), the production of 7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone significantly increased (Tsutsui et al., 2008).&nbsp;The opposite effect was observed on newt where melatonin stimulated 7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone synthesis (Koyama et al., 2009).&nbsp;  Similarly, orbital enucleation and pinealectomy performed on male quail, which abolished melatonin synthesis, induces a significant increase in 7&alpha;-hydroxypregnenolone concentration (Tsutsui et al., 2008). &nbsp;", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:01:35 +0000 2026"}